reviews.headline: Center of Attention not accurate
reviews.comments: I had this lipstick in the shade Centre of Attention for SO LONG and was so excited to see it on sale in 21 days of beauty!! It says it's supposed to be a bright yellow red - like other reviewers, what I got was instead a deep plum/brownish red. I checked the tube and the packaging and everything was labeled Centre of Attention but the lipstick did not match the description or the pictures on the website - it must have been a mistake. I was really devastated and made sure to let the Ulta employees when I returned it know that it was the wrong shade so that they didn't put it back on the shelf!

reviews.headline: Amorous
reviews.comments: Nice lipstick as you'd expect from MAC. The color was as described - a blue pink. For me, it will be an evening color, but if you are more bold, I can see this being a day color or even an everyday color. If your lips are in good shape, this is going to glide on and stay on nicely. If you are chapped, it will show more than a gloss. It is not moisturizing or drying, so will keep your lips in whatever condition they started.

reviews.headline: Bad bad bad color description for Centre of Attention
reviews.comments: The formula is pleasant and the package is sturdy. But oh boy, as a blind internet buy? Don't just don't believe the description for Centre of Attention - it is not a 'bright yellow based red".  It's a cool, deep, intense Bordeaux. I checked my package and the lipstick itself thinking this has to be a mistake. But no. So I returned it.

faceoff_positive.comments: It's been a while since I was excited about a new lipstick but this MACximal sleek satin lipstick in shade 'Truth Be Untold' is quickly becoming my everyday go-to. The formula is creamy and glides on easily, depending on how much color I want it can be a one and done or can be built up with multiple swipes. It's the perfect pinky-brown-nude for everyday with or without a liner. It feels hydrating and comfortable, even wearing it all day, it smooths out my lips and I don't find myself feeling like I need a balm over it. The color fades evenly and is easily given new life by applying a lip oil or gloss over it. I love the packaging, it feels sleek and solid, even though it's plastic it doesn't feel cheap. The cap clicks onto the tube securely and doesn't come off when it's rolling around my makeup bag or bottom of my purse. Overall, I'm extremely satisfied with it. The only reason that I'm giving it 4 It's been a while since I was excited about a new lipstick but this MACximal sleek satin lipstick in shade 'Truth Be Untold' is quickly becoming my everyday go-to. The formula is creamy and glides on easily, depending on how much color I want it can be a one and done or can be built up with multiple swipes. It's the perfect pinky-brown-nude for everyday with or without a liner. It feels hydrating and comfortable, even wearing it all day, it smooths out my lips and I don't find myself feeling like I need a balm over it. The color fades evenly and is easily given new life by applying a lip oil or gloss over it. I love the packaging, it feels sleek and solid, even though it's plastic it doesn't feel cheap. The cap clicks onto the tube securely and doesn't come off when it's rolling around my makeup bag or bottom of my purse. Overall, I'm extremely satisfied with it. The only reason that I'm giving it 4 instead of 5 stars is because of the fragrance, it's the classic vanilla but I just find it too artificial and strong, and because I wish that the color lasted longer.
faceoff_positive.headline: Creamy,  smoothing & hydrating

faceoff_negative.comments: Who loves free samples? THIS GIRL RIGHT HERE!! So thank you to MAC for letting me try out their Macximal Sleek Satin Lipstick in color Modesty. I have to say I was excited when I received my free sample and couldn't wait to write the review. And the first thing I noticed about this lipstick was the packaging and fortunately I don't mean this in a good way. The Box itself has an image of the lipstick on the outside of it and it could easily be confused with an adult Magic Bullet vibrating toy. And when I take it out of the packaging it's no better this isn't something that you want to pull out at work at a meeting. Although the lipstick itself is creamy and moisturizes and has good pigmentation, it comes off on everything. And I do mean everything. From your energy drink to your coffee or anything else lucky enough to have your lips on it, it will come off on it.
